FBIS4-11734 "drnes063_s_94012" FBIS-NES-94-063 Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 SOUTH ASIA Iran Passports To Take on New `Security Aspect' 1 Apr Passports To Take on New `Security Aspect' 1 Apr NC2903060494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 29 Mar 94 NC2903060494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] The Foreign Ministry's Information and Press Department has reported that ordinary, diplomatic, and service passports will change. So that passports are in line with the objectives and values of the Islamic Republic of Iran's system, as of 1 April, the anniversary of the establishment of the Islamic Republic of Iran, new passports will replace the current ones. The new passports will be different in size, shape, and in their security aspect from the existing documents and will be compiled by a computer in a way that will facilitate access to information and to references.
